The Russian anti-doping agency RUSADA, which does not meet the standards of the World Anti-Doping Agency, is not yet fully operational.
However, RUSADA can already conduct testing under the supervision of foreign experts and the British Anti-Doping Agency.
&quot;Even though progress has been made, much work remains to be done,&quot; said IAAF President Sebastian Coe.
The Russian Athletics Federation was suspended in November 2015, so Russian athletes lost last year&#39;s Olympic Games in Rio de Janeiro.
