&quot;I hope people get away with it, that our genome doesn&#39;t care who we are, and that genetic data is subjective and can be interpreted by everyone,&quot; Dewey-Hagborg said. You can also see her work Spurious Memories from 2007 on the topic of video.
&quot;DNA tells a lot of different stories, this is 30 of them.&quot;
The last copy of the exhibition, located in a separate room, is the only page from the above graphic novel.
